SIMPLE: unpope
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Unpope
<hw>Un*pope"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[1st pref.
<ets>un-</ets> + <ets>pope</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To divest of
the character, office, or authority of a pope.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To deprive of a pope.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Rome will never so far <qex>unpope</qex> herself as to part with
her pretended supremacy.</q> <rj><qau>Fuller.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Unportunate</ent>⟦br⟧
